{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480291","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480291"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:40:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:40:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"35"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17582405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17582405"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T06:41:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T06:41:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"35"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"35","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/35"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.06,0.68,0.18,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"35"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"24435"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"35","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/35"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"35"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"12414"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1984"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"10964"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5471"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6280"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41963"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"24435","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/24435"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 60-year-old man presents to his General Practitioner with a one week history\u0026nbsp;of waking at night gasping for air, on a background of six months of worsening general breathlessness with exertion. He has a\u0026nbsp;chronic cough, productive of clear/white sputum, and has gained four kilograms in weight over the past two months. He denies any chest pain and now maintains a healthy diet since he quit smoking one month ago. He has a history of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, type 2 diabetes, and atrial fibrillation. He has been taking a tapering course of prednisolone, however his dyspnoea has not responded. On examination, his oxygen saturation is 86% on mobilising, and 90% at rest. His pulse rate is 98/min, blood pressure 140/90mmHg, and temperature 36.7C. There is a scattered wheeze and bibasal crepitations. His chest X-ray is shown (Image). A complete blood examination shows: Hb 160 g/dL [115-155], WCC 11.5 x 10*9/L [4.00- 11], Plt 220 x 10*9/L [150-450].\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of this presentation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Sarcoidosis","Atypical pneumonia","Cardiac failure","Exacerbation of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease","Carcinoma of the lung"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has presented with a constellation of symptoms which are suggestive of \u003Cstrong\u003Ecardiac failure\u003C/strong\u003E, including the sudden onset dyspnoea on exertion, paroxysmal nocturnal dyspnoea and a productive cough with white sputum. The weight gain is in keeping with fluid retention and this additional symptom is supportive of the diagnosis of cardiac failure. All the other potential explanations for this patient\u0027s current symptoms would usually be associated with weight loss.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESarcoidosis\u003C/strong\u003E would present with dyspnoea on exertion, and a chronic cough (however this would usually  be a dry dry). Weight loss not weight gain would be expected. On imaging, there would be significant hilar lymphadenopathy which is not present in this patient\u0027s imaging.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has not experienced any fevers, headache, URTI symptoms and therefore make the diagnosis of \u003Cstrong\u003Eatypical pneumonia\u003C/strong\u003E less likely. There would also be a greater change in his FBC as well as experience a non-productive cough.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf this was an \u003Cstrong\u003Eexacerbation of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease\u003C/strong\u003E, an associated weight gain would not be expected and there may a greater response to prednisolone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile this patient is at high risk for a \u003Cstrong\u003Ecarcinoma of the lung\u003C/strong\u003E due to his smoking history, the patient currently has bilateral pleural effusions which would be atypical for this presentation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Cardiac failure can present with acute dyspnoea on exertion, paroxysmal nocturnal dyspnoea, productive cough and weight gain."],"references":["Watson, R. D., Gibbs, C. R., Lip, G. Y. ABC of heart failure. Clinical features and complications.\u00a0BMJ (Clinical research ed.) [Internet]. BMJ 2000 [cited 19 April 2022].  https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.320.7229.236","Kuzniar, T. Assessment of Chronic Cough. BMJ Best Practice; 2022.\u00a0[7 April 2022; 19 April 2022]. Available from: https://bestpractice-bmj-com.ezproxy.une.edu.au/topics/en-gb/69"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"12414"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"35"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15620"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15620","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15620"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ac62230f-8fd0-4665-8c48-3bf21e5be277.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ac62230f-8fd0-4665-8c48-3bf21e5be277.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":564}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"12414","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/12414"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2022-06-05T15:32:56+09:30","updatedAt":"2022-06-05T15:32:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"35"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"24435"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms